						               													<description>&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;        GAME SYSTEM&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;    &amp;#10;         This entry is to allow for discussion/rating of the game system as a whole. It is not for a specific product or release. Versions will appear on the individual item pages.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Future Card Buddyfight is a Japanese collectible card game from the same creators as CardFight!! Vanguard and Wei&amp;#195;&amp;#159; Schwarz. It was released in January 2014 alongside an anime series by the same name. A manga adaptation began circulation in November 2013.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In it, players take turns playing monsters and other cards in an attempt to reduce the opponents life points to 0. Monsters are played in one of three zones&amp;mdash;center, right, left. If the center space is empty, that player is vulnerable to attack.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are five card types: Flags, Items, Monsters, Impacts, and Spells. A player&amp;rsquo;s deck consists of 52 cards: 1 Buddy (a monster card), 1 Flag&amp;mdash;both of which start the game in play&amp;mdash;and a main deck of 50 cards which cannot contain more than four copies of any given card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1 booster box contains 30 booster packs. Each pack contains 5 random cards. The rarities of cards are categorized into Common (C), Uncommon (UC), Rare (R), Double Rare (RR), Triple Rare (RRR), Buddy Rare (BR) and Special Parallel (SP).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
